# Geometry validation after CSG changes

## After any CSG rewrite

1. Export STLs for the affected part (`make build` or render in Docker)
2. Compare bounding box, volume, and genus against the baseline before your change
3. Hull rewrites and `linear_extrude` substitutions can change genus (e.g. genus 0 to 1) even when the visual shape looks equivalent — always verify

## `_fn` visibility rule

Before reducing `_fn` on any `sphere()`, `cylinder()`, or `rotate_extrude()`:
- Trace whether the shape is visible in the final mesh or fully consumed by a boolean cut
- Visible surfaces (e.g. nail bed sphere in `part_tip`) must keep default or higher `_fn` — low values produce visible faceting
- Cutting geometry and hull anchors can safely use lower `_fn`

## Visual verification

- Run `make verify-web-ui` and read the screenshot — exit code 0 is not proof of visual correctness
- For geometry-only checks without the viewer, compare STL checksums or use bbox/volume from `geometry_checks.py`
